Be6 9. Be3 Be7 10. c3 O-O 11. Nbd2 Qd7 12. Re1 $5 {This is intended as a
subtle move, not forcing anything yet.} Nxd2 $1 {The simplest reaction to the
bishop's delay on b3.} (12... Rad8 {is generally useful, but lacks concrete
impact, thus justifying White's last move:} 13. Bc2 Nxd2 14. Qxd2 Bg4 15. Qd3
g6 16. Bh6 Rfe8 17. Rad1 $14 {Kamsky,G (2710) -Piket,J (2670) Dos Hermanas
1995 CBM 047 [Wedberg] (1-0, 35). Unlike in the main game, Black does not have
